{"id":"1801.07799","submitter":"Suddhasattwa Das","authors":"Suddhasattwa Das, Dimitrios Giannakis","title":"Koopman spectra in reproducing kernel Hilbert spaces","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.acha.2020.05.008","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Every invertible, measure-preserving dynamical system induces a Koopman\noperator, which is a linear, unitary evolution operator acting on the $L^2$\nspace of observables associated with the invariant measure. Koopman\neigenfunctions represent the quasiperiodic, or non-mixing, component of the\ndynamics. The extraction of these eigenfunctions and their associated\neigenfrequencies from a given time series is a non-trivial problem when the\nunderlying system has a dense point spectrum, or a continuous spectrum behaving\nsimilarly to noise. This paper describes methods for identifying Koopman\neigenfrequencies and eigenfunctions from a discretely sampled time series\ngenerated by such a system with unknown dynamics. Our main result gives\nnecessary and sufficient conditions for a Fourier function, defined on $N$\nstates sampled along an orbit of the dynamics, to be extensible to a Koopman\neigenfunction on the whole state space, lying in a reproducing kernel Hilbert\nspace (RKHS). In particular, we show that such an extension exists if and only\nif the RKHS norm of the Fourier function does not diverge as $ N \\to \\infty $,\nin which case the corresponding Fourier frequency is also a Koopman\neigenfrequency. If such an RKHS extension does not exist, we can still\nconstruct an $L^2$ approximation of the eigenfunction. Numerical experiments on\nmixed-spectrum systems with weak periodic components demonstrate that this\napproach has significantly higher skill in identifying Koopman eigenfrequencies\ncompared to conventional spectral estimation techniques based on the discrete\nFourier transform.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Jan 2018 22:38:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Jan 2018 17:41:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 16 Apr 2018 10:28:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 1 Jun 2018 15:54:36 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 19 May 2019 18:33:55 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Wed, 19 Jun 2019 13:08:55 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 23 Jul 2019 23:50:49 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 12 Nov 2019 19:53:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-26"}
